From d3f4d76604851024b8c48b61c088ee5979eff904 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Mohd Ayaan Anwar <mohd.anwar@oss.qualcomm.com>
Date: Mon, 16 Mar 2026 14:05:12 +0530
Subject: [PATCH 12/12] net: ethernet: tc956x: Add Qualcomm platform driver and
 GPIO controller

The TC956X PCIe Ethernet bridge (QPS615) needs SoC-specific glue on
Qualcomm platforms.  Add two new files:

tc956x_qcom.c implements the tc956x_platform_{probe,remove,suspend,
resume}() hooks.  It parses phy-reset-gpios, an optional phy-supply
regulator, pinctrl default state, and WoL IRQ from the device tree.
On suspend, the WoL IRQ is armed as a wakeup source when WoL is active;
otherwise the PHY is powered down.

tc956x_gpio.c registers a gpio_chip backed by the TC956X internal GPIO
block.  Registration is restricted to port 0 so only one PF owns the
controller.

Remove the old tc956x_platform_probe() and tc956x_platform_resume()
stubs from tc956xmac_main.c, which contained hard-coded RBTC9563_3MA
board-specific GPIO toggles.  Convert the CONFIG_TC956X_PLATFORM_SUPPORT
\#else stubs in tc956xmac.h to proper static-inline no-ops.

Upstream-Status: Submitted [https://github.com/TC956X/TC9564_Host_Driver/pull/6]
Signed-off-by: Mohd Ayaan Anwar <mohd.anwar@oss.qualcomm.com>
Signed-off-by: Ricardo Salveti <ricardo.salveti@oss.qualcomm.com>
